    <item id="import-auto-id1677107">An isolated system is defined to be one for which the net external force is zero <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mfenced open="(" close=")"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext mathvariant="bold">F</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>net</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mfenced><m:mtext>.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ left (F rSub { size 8{ ital "net"} } =0 right ) "." } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1788788">During projectile motion and where air resistance is negligible, momentum is conserved in the horizontal direction because horizontal forces are zero.</item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1179529">Conservation of momentum applies only when the net external force is zero.</item>
