<para id="eip-id2276364"><emphasis>Professional Application</emphasis></para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1505969">Train cars are coupled together by being bumped into one another. Suppose two loaded train cars are moving toward one another, the first having a mass of 150,000 kg and a velocity of 0.300 m/s, and the second having a mass of 110,000 kg and a velocity of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>120 m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ - 0 "." "120"`"m/s"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. (The minus indicates direction of motion.) What is their final velocity?</para></problem>
